// Semantic direction:
// otel is the OpenTelemetry SDK that provides vendor-neutral observability primitives.
// otel_resource identifies the service producing telemetry: service_name, version, environment.
// tracer creates spans; tracer_provider manages tracer instances and their exporters.
// span is one unit of work within a distributed trace, with start and end timestamps.
// trace_id identifies the end-to-end trace; parent_span links nested operations.
// span_kind indicates the role: server (handling a request), client (calling another service).
// span_attr are key-value labels that add context (HTTP method, DB query, error message).
// span_event is a timestamped annotation within a span (e.g. "cache miss", "retry attempt").
// span_link connects causally related spans across independent traces.
// context_propagation passes the trace_context across process boundaries.
// traceparent and tracestate are the W3C standard headers for HTTP context propagation.
// extract_context reads trace context from incoming request headers.
// inject_context writes trace context into outgoing request headers.
// counter is a monotonically increasing metric (requests, errors, bytes sent).
// histogram records the distribution of values (latency, request size).
// gauge records the current value of a resource (active connections, queue depth).
// exemplar links a specific trace to a histogram bucket for correlating metrics and traces.
// log_record carries a severity level, body text, and key-value attributes.
// log_span_context links a log record to the span that was active when it was emitted.
// otlp_exporter sends telemetry to an OpenTelemetry collector via gRPC or HTTP.
// prometheus_exporter exposes metric data in Prometheus scrape format on an HTTP endpoint.
// export_batch accumulates telemetry for batch_interval before sending, with a batch_size limit.

// Primitive flow:
// service startup: otel_sdk init -> otel_resource (service_name, version) -> provider setup
// incoming request: extract_context(headers) -> trace_context
// -> tracer.start_span(name, parent=trace_context) -> span
// -> business logic runs -> span_attr set, span_event recorded
// -> outgoing call: inject_context(headers) -> propagate to downstream service
// -> span_end -> exporter batch
// metrics: counter.add(1, attr) / histogram.record(latency_ms) per operation
// logging: logger.info("message", attr) + log_span_context links to active span
// export: batch_interval fires -> otlp_exporter.send(spans + metrics + logs) -> collector
// prometheus: GET /metrics -> prometheus_exporter scrapes meter_provider -> Prometheus format

// This defines OpenTelemetry-based distributed tracing, metrics, and structured
// logging with W3C context propagation and OTLP export.
